<h4>Bespoke Rendering &amp; Block Format</h4>
<p>
  The world is your oyster, especially now that Ember has give us <i>contextual components</i> which really open up creativity to do almost anything with the options menu.
</p>

<div class="row downer">
  <div class="col-xs-6 col-md-4">
    {{#select-input
      options=model
      searchField='name,email'
      renderTemplate='name-email'
      optgroups=optGroup
      as |s|
    }}
      {{s.option '> [[item.name]]'}}
      {{#s.item}}
        <span class='option-avatar'>
          <span>
            <img src="[[item.object.avatar]]" class='.option-icon' style='height: 2.0rem; width: 2.0rem; border-radius: 50%;'>
          </span>
          <span style='width: 0.5rem'></span>
          <span>
            [[item.name]]
          </span>
        </span>
      {{/s.item}}
      {{#s.group}}
        <b>
          {{ui-icon 'bars'}}
          [[item.group]]
        </b>
      {{/s.group}}
    {{/select-input}}
  </div>
</div>
